Here is the solution using Julia language:

```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return lowercase(replace(strip(col), r"[\s-]" => "_"))
end

# Test the function
@assert clean_column("My Column") == "my_column"
```

In this solution, we define a function `clean_column` that takes a column name as input and returns the cleaned version of it. We use the `strip` function to remove leading and trailing whitespaces, `lowercase` to convert all characters to lowercase, and `replace` with a regular expression to replace all spaces and hyphens with an underscore. We also test the function with the given data to ensure it works as expected.
